Mix undrained tomatoes and tomato paste in slow cooker until blended. Stir in vegetables. Cut meat into 8 pieces; pound to 1/2-inch thickness. Sprinkle with oregano. Add to slow cooker; press into sauce with back of spoon. Cover with lid; cook on LOW 4 to 4 1/2 hours or on HIGH 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Cook pasta as directed on package, omitting salt. Transfer meat to plate, reserving sauce in slow cooker; cover meat to keep warm. Mix cornstarch and water until blended. Add to sauce; stir. Cook, covered, on HIGH 6 to 8 minutes or until thickened. Drain pasta; spoon onto serving plates. Top with meat, sauce and cheeses.